.TH SDL_CreateTextureWithProperties 3 "SDL 3.0.0" "SDL" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_CreateTextureWithProperties \- Create a texture for a rendering context with the specified properties\[char46]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "SDL_Texture* SDL_CreateTextureWithProperties(SDL_Renderer *renderer, SDL_PropertiesID props);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
These are the supported properties:


\(bu "format" (number) - one of the enumerated values in
  
.BR SDL_PixelFormatEnum
, defaults to the best RGBA
  format for the renderer

\(bu "access" (number) - one of the enumerated values in
  
.BR SDL_TextureAccess
, defaults to
  
.BR SDL_TEXTUREACCESS_STATIC


\(bu "width" (number) - the width of the texture in pixels, required

\(bu "height" (number) - the height of the texture in pixels, required

With the direct3d11 renderer:


\(bu "d3d11\[char46]texture" (pointer) - the ID3D11Texture2D associated with the
  texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "d3d11\[char46]texture_u" (pointer) - the ID3D11Texture2D associated with the U
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "d3d11\[char46]texture_v" (pointer) - the ID3D11Texture2D associated with the V
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

With the direct3d12 renderer:


\(bu "d3d12\[char46]texture" (pointer) - the ID3D12Resource associated with the
  texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "d3d12\[char46]texture_u" (pointer) - the ID3D12Resource associated with the U
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "d3d12\[char46]texture_v" (pointer) - the ID3D12Resource associated with the V
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

With the opengl renderer:


\(bu "opengl\[char46]texture" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the
  texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "opengl\[char46]texture_uv" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the UV
  plane of an NV12 texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "opengl\[char46]texture_u" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the U
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "opengl\[char46]texture_v" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the V
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

With the opengles2 renderer:


\(bu "opengles2\[char46]texture" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the
  texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "opengles2\[char46]texture_uv" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the
  UV plane of an NV12 texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "opengles2\[char46]texture_u" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the U
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

\(bu "opengles2\[char46]texture_v" (number) - the GLuint texture associated with the V
  plane of a YUV texture, if you want to wrap an existing texture\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I renderer
the rendering context
.TP
.I props
the properties to use
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a pointer to the created texture or NULL if no rendering context
was active, the format was unsupported, or the width or height were out of
range; call 
.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

